@AudriusButkevicius  YES. 

@Zillode   like: curl -X POST -H "X-API-Key: xxxx" http://localhost:8384/rest/db/scan\?folder\=Sync&sub\=test

After I change file in other folder(not int test folder), run this POST, the whole folder Sync will be scanned.

BTW, I'm trying to us fswatch(https://github.com/emcrisostomo/fswatch) to detect changing file and tell Syncthing to scan these files.( I'd like a real-time synchronizing but to small scan interval would bring lots unnecessary costs )
